      "author_association" : "NONE",
      "body" : "> Thanks for your contribution. However the systemd service file _should_ work on Ubuntu. If it does not at this time for you, it would be good to fix that.\r\n> \r\n> I don't think including an old sysv-style init script is the right solution. Systemd contains some fallbacks to support this but that's at most a temporary situation, I suspect.\r\n\r\nYou can't adapt the existing script to work on any operating system using Systemd, for example the script bitcoind.init uses the file /etc/init.d/functions to get generic initialization functions which is specific to Redhat and doesn't exist on Debian/Ubuntu.\r\nDepending on the operating system you want to support you can replace the existing script by mine, or reject my merge request.",
